Loop iter23 (2026-05-25): ROOT CAUSE of why JS wrapper fixes appear not to work in practice. The installed ~/.gm-tools/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js was NOT refreshed when gm-plugkit published a new version (no wasm bump = no update_available signal), so running watchers kept stale wrapper code. lib/skill-bootstrap.js had ensureSupervisorInstalled() and SKILL.md auto-refresh but NO equivalent for the wrapper itself. FIX: added ensureWrapperInstalled() (sha-compare bundled-or-npm wrapper vs installed, atomic tmp+rename) wired into the bootstrap sequence after ensureSupervisorInstalled, so every gm-skill session refreshes the installed wrapper. This is the half that WRITES the refresh; the wrapper's own 60s drift-self-respawn interval is the half that PICKS IT UP at runtime, but that detector silently no-opped under a long-running direct-no-supervisor watcher (deferred: wrapper-drift-detector-missed-installed-file-change). Validated: manual refresh changed installed sha 455b45f3->06be66de (browser.stale-reclaimed 0->1), fresh boot pid 220296 loaded it. LESSON: a JS fix to gm-plugkit/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js does NOT reach running watchers until the installed copy is refreshed AND the watcher reboots; verify both, not just the push.